# Workflows & CLI

- **Workflows** (ordered checklists): `.cursor/workflows/` — read `README.md` then the matching file
- **Skills** (domain depth): `.cursor/skills/` — e.g. `push-notifications`, `cli-first`
- **Rules** (constraints): `.cursor/rules/` — this folder

When the user asks to ship, promote, deploy, add push, validate a contract, run Loop A/B, or **start a validation chain** → open the relevant workflow first (`validate-contract.md` for contract loops).

**Validation chain (one Agent chat):** User says `Run ./.cursor/hooks/validation-loop-start.sh <contract-id> and complete Validator this turn` → run the script, then validate in the same turn; write `docs/contracts/.validation-session.json` when done. Hook chains Fixer only on fail.

**CLI first:** If `gh`, `supabase`, `eas`, `git`, or `npm` can do the job, run it yourself. Read `.cursor/skills/cli-first/SKILL.md` when unsure.
